claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: A flowchart showing the number of study participants aged 18–64 vaccinated in each flu season (2018–2021), divided into those receiving a recombinant influenza vaccine versus a standard-dose vaccine, with sequential exclusion criteria leading to the final analytic cohorts and age breakdowns. The figure is a participant flow diagram and does not provide any data on hemagglutinin antigen content or comparative immunogenicity, and therefore does not support the claim. Note: None
